In [5]:
past=7*4 #According to the data in the four last weeks,
future=7 #We will predict the value in the next week
In [6]:
values=money.curs #This is the value we want to predict
In [7]:
start=past
end=len(values)-future
In [8]:
print(f"We will start from {start} days ago and will predict data till the {end} days")

We will start from 28 days ago and will predict data till the 510 days
In [9]:
days=end-start
print("We will predict values for ", days, "days")

We will predict values for  482 days
In [10]:
raw_df=[]
for i in range(start, end):
    past_and_future_values=values[(i-past):(i+future)] #Data with we work with (4 weeks past and the next one)
    raw_df.append(list(past_and_future_values))

In [83]:
Maximo=0
Minimo=100
maxpos=0 #Maximum position
minpos=0 #Minimum position
for i in range(1,len(error)):
    num=error[i]
    if(num>Maximo):
        Maximo=num
        maxpos=i
    elif(num<Minimo):
        Minimo=num
        minpos=i
print("Maximum error",Maximo, "and this corresponds to ", nombre[maxpos])
print("Minimum error",Minimo, "and this corresponds to ", nombre[minpos])

Maximum error 41.22739605181159 and this corresponds to  Gaussian Process
Minimum error 0.3993240787900975 and this corresponds to  Random Forest without random_state
